<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1073,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,324,1073,1098]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Redescription.</emphasis>
Body generally reddish brown, with deep punctures (
<figureCitation box="[978,1093,1073,1097]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,217,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ventocoris horvathi (Puton, 1896) a, b, c) 3 body, (dorsal view), d) Ƥ body, (dorsal view), e) 3 Head (dorsal view), f) 3 antenna, g) Pygophore (Ventral view), h) Pygophore (Top view), i) Paramera (Lateral view), j) 3 Orifice, k) Ƥ genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247991/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Figures 
<number box="[1078,1093,1073,1097]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
. a, b, c, d). Ocellus closely approaching distal margin of pronotum, head orange or reddish-brown, with punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1164,1274,1109,1133]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,217,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ventocoris horvathi (Puton, 1896) a, b, c) 3 body, (dorsal view), d) Ƥ body, (dorsal view), e) 3 Head (dorsal view), f) 3 antenna, g) Pygophore (Ventral view), h) Pygophore (Top view), i) Paramera (Lateral view), j) 3 Orifice, k) Ƥ genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247991/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Figures 
<number box="[1259,1274,1109,1133]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
. e). Antennae yellow, without conspicuous setae, antennal segment 
<number box="[748,762,1145,1169]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1.0">1</number>
extending to apex of head (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1180,1145,1169]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,217,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ventocoris horvathi (Puton, 1896) a, b, c) 3 body, (dorsal view), d) Ƥ body, (dorsal view), e) 3 Head (dorsal view), f) 3 antenna, g) Pygophore (Ventral view), h) Pygophore (Top view), i) Paramera (Lateral view), j) 3 Orifice, k) Ƥ genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247991/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Figures 
<number box="[1165,1180,1145,1169]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
. e, f). Rostrum yellow, the apical two segments black, its apex extending to or passing hind coxae. Thoracic pleuron yellowish brown and punctured. Pronotum separated by a transverse line into two regions. Distal margin and proximal portion of pronotum reddish-brown, distal region yellow. Scutellum extends to end of abdomen and usually with yellow, orange or redish brown triangular mark; connexivum yellow, connexival tubercles absent (
<figureCitation box="[1192,1302,1289,1313]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,217,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ventocoris horvathi (Puton, 1896) a, b, c) 3 body, (dorsal view), d) Ƥ body, (dorsal view), e) 3 Head (dorsal view), f) 3 antenna, g) Pygophore (Ventral view), h) Pygophore (Top view), i) Paramera (Lateral view), j) 3 Orifice, k) Ƥ genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247991/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Figures 
<number box="[1287,1302,1289,1313]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
. a, b, c, d). Abdominal dorsum black, abdominal venter, spiracles and legs yellow. Metathoracic scent gland ostiole associated with peritreme as other subgenera 
<taxonomicName box="[537,655,1362,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Ventocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[537,655,1362,1385]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Ventocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[670,767,1361,1385]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,217,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ventocoris horvathi (Puton, 1896) a, b, c) 3 body, (dorsal view), d) Ƥ body, (dorsal view), e) 3 Head (dorsal view), f) 3 antenna, g) Pygophore (Ventral view), h) Pygophore (Top view), i) Paramera (Lateral view), j) 3 Orifice, k) Ƥ genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247991/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Figure 
<number box="[752,767,1361,1385]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
. j).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1073,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,373,1397,1422]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Ventral view of pygophore dark brown, medial region of ventral rim of pygophore little concave (
<figureCitation box="[262,363,1433,1457]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,217,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ventocoris horvathi (Puton, 1896) a, b, c) 3 body, (dorsal view), d) Ƥ body, (dorsal view), e) 3 Head (dorsal view), f) 3 antenna, g) Pygophore (Ventral view), h) Pygophore (Top view), i) Paramera (Lateral view), j) 3 Orifice, k) Ƥ genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247991/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Figure 
<number box="[348,363,1433,1457]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
. g, h). Apex of paramere slender and curved up, lateral edge of paramere with very small tubercle (
<figureCitation box="[256,352,1469,1493]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,217,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ventocoris horvathi (Puton, 1896) a, b, c) 3 body, (dorsal view), d) Ƥ body, (dorsal view), e) 3 Head (dorsal view), f) 3 antenna, g) Pygophore (Ventral view), h) Pygophore (Top view), i) Paramera (Lateral view), j) 3 Orifice, k) Ƥ genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247991/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Figure 
<number box="[337,352,1469,1493]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1.0">
<date box="[337,352,1469,1493]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">1</date>
</number>
</figureCitation>
. i).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1073,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,400,1505,1530]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Female genitalia</emphasis>
: Female genitalia as illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[816,927,1505,1529]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,217,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ventocoris horvathi (Puton, 1896) a, b, c) 3 body, (dorsal view), d) Ƥ body, (dorsal view), e) 3 Head (dorsal view), f) 3 antenna, g) Pygophore (Ventral view), h) Pygophore (Top view), i) Paramera (Lateral view), j) 3 Orifice, k) Ƥ genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247991/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Figures 
<number box="[912,927,1505,1529]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
. k, 
<number box="[978,990,1505,1529]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="8.0">8</number>
th gonocoxite black, laterally red, 
<number box="[1400,1413,1505,1529]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="9.0">9</number>
th gonocoxite brown, punctured.
</paragraph>
