<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="155" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1073,2033]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="155" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1865,1890]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Comments.</emphasis>
This Irano-Turanian species was described from the surroundings of 
<collectingCountry box="[1150,1218,1866,1890]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Hatay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1233,1315,1865,1889]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. It is rare, distributed according to the available records only in East 
<collectingCountry box="[803,899,1901,1925]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
and the Mediterranean region of 
<collectingCountry box="[1274,1354,1901,1925]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Puton" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" refString="Puton, A. (1896) Hemipteres nouveaux. Revue d'Entomologie 12, 232 - 234." type="journal article" year="1896">
Puton 
<number box="[151,210,1937,1961]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1896.0">1896</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Onder" box="[222,423,1937,1961]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" refString="Onder, F., Karsavuran, Y., Tezcan, S. &amp; Fent, M. (2006) Turkiye Heteroptera (Insecta) Katalo g u. Meta Basim Matbaacilik Hizmetleri, Izmir, 164 pp. (In Turkish with English summary)." type="book" year="2006">
Önder 
<emphasis box="[299,348,1937,1961]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[362,423,1937,1961]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It is variable in colour, especially in the triangular mark of the scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1375,1937,1961]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,217,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ventocoris horvathi (Puton, 1896) a, b, c) 3 body, (dorsal view), d) Ƥ body, (dorsal view), e) 3 Head (dorsal view), f) 3 antenna, g) Pygophore (Ventral view), h) Pygophore (Top view), i) Paramera (Lateral view), j) 3 Orifice, k) Ƥ genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247991/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
Figures 
<number box="[1360,1375,1937,1961]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
. a, b, c, d). The structure of pygophore and paramere of this species is different from those of 
<emphasis box="[1146,1271,1974,1997]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<taxonomicName box="[1146,1266,1974,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Cimicidae" genus="Cimex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rusticus">V. rusticus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Medial region of ventral rim of pygophore of 
<taxonomicName box="[495,617,2009,2033]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Trigonosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horvathi">
<emphasis box="[495,617,2009,2033]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">V. horvathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
slightly concave, apex of paramere slender and curved up, lateral edge of paramere with very small tubercle (
<figureCitation box="[563,662,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,217,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ventocoris horvathi (Puton, 1896) a, b, c) 3 body, (dorsal view), d) Ƥ body, (dorsal view), e) 3 Head (dorsal view), f) 3 antenna, g) Pygophore (Ventral view), h) Pygophore (Top view), i) Paramera (Lateral view), j) 3 Orifice, k) Ƥ genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247991/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
Figure 
<number box="[647,662,151,175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
. g, i). Medial region of ventral rim of pygophore of 
<taxonomicName authority="Vshaped" authorityName="Vshaped" class="Insecta" family="Cimicidae" genus="Cimex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rusticus">
<emphasis box="[1280,1399,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">V. rusticus</emphasis>
Vshaped
</taxonomicName>
, apex of paramere shwollenly and upswept, lateral edge of paramere concave (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1255,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1780,1803]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,205,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,175,1759]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ventocoris rusticus (Fabricius, 1781) pygophore: (Venral view a-e; top view f-j); a, f) as V. a dv e na from Ukraina, b, h) as V. trigonus from Turkey, c, g) as V. r a m b u r i from Spain, d, j) as V. rusticus from Italy, e, i) as V. nigellae from Algeria." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247996/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
Figures 
<number box="[1238,1255,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
. and 
<figureCitation box="[1319,1337,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[186,1409,230,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,177,1858]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Ventocoris rusticus (Fabricius, 1781) paramera: a, j) as V. advena from Ukraina, b) as V. nigellae from Algeria, c, h) as V. ra m b ur i from Spain, d) as V. rusticus from Italy, e) as V. trigonus from Turkey (European part), f) as V. trigonus from Turkey (Black sea region), g) as V. trigonus from Turkey (European part), i) as V. rusticus from Italy." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247997/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
<number box="[1319,1337,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
.). It was captured on 
<taxonomicName box="[289,371,224,248]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Nigella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[289,371,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Nigella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName box="[425,598,223,247]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Ranunculaceae</taxonomicName>
) in 
<collectingCountry box="[641,721,223,247]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Horvath" box="[736,896,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" refString="Horvath, G. (1896) Notes sur le genre Trigonosoma. Revue d'Entomologie, 15, 1 - 231." type="journal article" year="1896">
Horváth 
<number box="[837,896,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" value="1896.0">1896</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoberlandt" box="[907,1100,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" refString="Hoberlandt, L. (1956) Results of the Zoological Scientific Expedition of the National Museum in Prague to Turkey. 18. Hemiptera IV. Terrestrial Hemiptera-Heteroptera of Turkey. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, Supplementum, 3 (1955), 1 - 264." type="journal article" year="1956">
Hoberlandt 
<number box="[1040,1100,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" value="1956.0">1956</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
